news_header: NATO defence ministers meet in Brussels with Ukrainian President Zelensky presenting his victory plan.
news_text: NATO defence ministers are convening in Brussels on Thursday and Friday, where Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky is set to present his victory plan to political leaders. NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte has not fully endorsed Zelensky's peace plan, indicating a need for more information. This meeting will also see the participation of NATO's partner countries from the Indopasif region for the first time, with Finland represented by Minister of Defence Antti Häkkänen.
